The South African Social Security Agency's is warning social grant recipients against a new scam, which gives fraudsters access to grant money in their accounts. People posing as government employees are asking to 'check' whether the beneficiaries' bank card is still active. Fraudsters then use a skimming device to steal vital information and clone the card. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Social Security Agency is warning social grant recipients about a new scam, which gives fraudsters access to grant money in their accounts. READ: SAPO branch closures won't affect Sassa grant recipients Scamsters masquerading as employees of the agency are skimming personal information off recipients Sassa cards, which then allows them to clone the card, and steal the money. Sassa says as soon as they got wind of the scam law enforcement agencies were alerted.